Qatar Islamic Quarterly Profit Rises 7% on Financing Income

-- B y   A r i f   S h a r i f
-- 
2011-04-13T12:04:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/qatar-islamic-quarterly-profit-rises-7-on-financing-income-1-.html
Qatar Islamic Bank (QIBK)  SAQ, the
Persian Gulf country’s biggest Shariah-compliant lender,
reported a 7 percent gain in first-quarter profit as financing
income increased.  Net income rose to 321 million riyals ($88 million) from
300 million riyals in the year-earlier period, the Doha-based
bank said in an e-mailed statement today. Analysts at EFG Hermes
Holding SAE had estimated profit of 335 million riyals.  Net financing income grew 8.6 percent to 457 million
riyals, while fee income dropped 22 percent to 65 million
riyals, the Qatari lender said today. The bank’s Islamic loan
book expanded 3.2 percent to 24.7 billion riyals, and customers’
current and investment accounts grew 1.5 percent to 25.7 billion
riyals, it said.  Qatar Islamic Bank rose 0.8 percent to close at 83.6 riyals
on the Doha exchange today. The shares have risen 3.9 percent
this year, giving the company a market value of about 19.8
billion riyals.  To contact the reporters on this story:
